Clemens, D. P., Cashman, L. R., Cerny, C., El-Batal, A. M., Jameson, K. E., Marchwinski, R., Montgomery, J., Pavel, M., Pinnick, A., & Taylor, B. W. (2020). The Galactic Plane Infrared Polarization Survey (GPIPS): Data Release 4. The Astrophysical Journal Supplement Series, 249(2), 23–23. https://doi.org/10.3847/1538-4365/ab9f30
/Access to data: https://irsa.ipac.caltech.edu/data/GPIPS/catalog/ (used in this study: GPIPS_DR4_Unique_Star_File.tbl)
/access to info on data comprehension: https://irsa.ipac.caltech.edu/data/GPIPS/gator_docs/gpipsdr4_colDescriptions.html#:~:text=Overview,the%201.8%20m%20Perkins%20telescope.
//GPIPS DR4 provides H-band (1.6 μm) photometry and polarimetry for over 13 million stars across the northern Galactic plane, observed with the Mimir instrument on the 1.8m Perkins telescope.
/The files in /data are subsets of (GPIPS_DR4_Unique_Star_File.tbl) using student-created expressions. They were used to create different scales of maps using the TOPCAT Table Browser and Sky Map. (More info on TOPCAT: https://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/topcat/) 

